        "title": "How to cancel long running query in PostgreSQL with JDBC?",
        "body": "<p>In my project i have some legacy plugins. These plugins used for read only queries from PostgreSQL. Most of plugins works well, but other part is really slow. It's reason for hangups on acquiring connection from C3P0.\nIt's looks like changes for connection timeout on pool has no effect.<\/p>\n\n<p>How i can set timeout for effective cancelation these queries? \nI think timeout for server side can be nice solution but i don't want set timeouts for all server in configs. Also i don't want drop this connection and need cancel current query only.<\/p>\n\n<p>Can you share your ideas about solution for this problem? <\/p>\n",
        "question_id": 31359000,
        "tags": [
            "java",
            "postgresql"
        ],
        "score": 3,
        "is_answered": true,
        "view_count": 5870,
        "last_edit_date": 1452609029
